      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH, defined as the ratio of device NIH to predicate NIH, directly addresses the COU decision of whether the CPB pump produces equivalent or lower hemolysis than the predicate device. The QoI is clinically meaningful and maps directly to the regulatory acceptance criterion."
